This paper discusses the efficient utilization of wireless network resources for the Future Internet, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The proposed mechanism is an auction-based approach, which involves game theory and optimization, making it relevant to the sub-category of game theory and economics (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the computational complexity and message overhead of the proposed mechanism, which relates to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper mentions simulations that assess the proposed mechanism's performance, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
